<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><map version="1.0.1"><node TEXT="Q-Chain"><node TEXT="analytics"><node TEXT="ID:Q-008 | T:What ETL strategies and integration approaches are outlined in the ETL and strategy documents? | C: | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review ETL_Audit_Columns_Strategy_v2.1.md and Integration_Design_v1.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Review SCD_Strategy_v2.1.md and Snapshot_Strategy_2.1.md"/><node TEXT="- Review schema_lint.py for validation logic"/></node></node><node TEXT="documentation"><node TEXT="ID:Q-011 | T:What data storage infrastructure is available (SQL Express or Fabric) and how should we provision it for the warehouse? | C: | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Confirm whether SQL Express is installed on the VM or accessible elsewhere"/><node TEXT="- Assess if Microsoft Fabric’s free warehouse tier can serve as the target database"/><node TEXT="- Identify storage limits, connectivity requirements and any setup steps needed"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-012 | T:How will we compile and deliver the final YAML summaries for all 19 project documents? | C: | S:asked | D:high | Depends:Q-006,Q-007,Q-008,Q-009,Q-010"><node TEXT="- Define the YAML schema for each document summary, ensuring consistency with existing plan_zero and project_charter formats"/><node TEXT="- Review and extract key information from each of the 19 documents, noting definitions, requirements, assumptions and tasks"/><node TEXT="- Draft and validate YAML files, incorporating feedback and iterating as needed"/><node TEXT="- Document any gaps or uncertainties for follow‑up"/></node></node><node TEXT="environment"><node TEXT="ID:Q-010 | T:What operational setup and lessons are captured in the landing and storyboard documents? | C: | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review README_landing.md and Storyboard.md"/><node TEXT="- Review Plan zero.md and any related README files"/><node TEXT="- Summarise landing zone setup, retention policies, conventions and lessons learned"/></node></node><node TEXT="etl"><node TEXT="ID:Q-007 | T:What data model structures and specifications are defined in the data‑model and spec documents? | C: | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review Retail_Data_Model_v2.1.md and Retail_Data_Model_v2.1.dbml.txt"/><node TEXT="- Review Data-Spec_Sheet_v3.3.1.md and Data_Design_v1.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Summarise entities, attributes, relationships and constraints"/></node></node><node TEXT="misc"><node TEXT="ID:Q-XXX | T:Your question here | C: | S:unasked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- MECE bullet"/></node></node><node TEXT="model"><node TEXT="ID:Q-006 | T:What are the key points and objectives described in the vision and charter documents? | C: | S:answered | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Read Vision.md, Project Charter.txt, plan_zero.yaml and project_charter.yaml"/><node TEXT="- Summarise the vision, objectives, scope and timeline"/><node TEXT="- Capture any strategic assumptions or constraints"/></node></node><node TEXT="operations"><node TEXT="ID:Q-009 | T:What KPIs, metrics and definitions are provided in the KPI and trace documents? | C: | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review KPI List v3.0.md and KPI_Cards v3.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Review KPI_Trace_Matrix_v3.0.md and Data_KPI_Trace_Matrix_v3.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Summarise definitions, calculations, dimensions and fact mappings"/></node></node><node TEXT="planning"><node TEXT="ID:Q-001 | T:How should we structure the Q‑Chain to manage the retail data warehouse and analytics project based on the uploaded documents? | C: | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review all 19 uploaded project files (vision, design docs, KPI lists, audit strategy, etc.)"/><node TEXT="- Identify major questions, tasks and deliverables needed to build the retail data warehouse and KPI dashboards"/><node TEXT="- Define dependencies and decision points across phases (ETL, modelling, dashboarding, governance)"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-002 | T:How should we systematically review and summarise the content of all uploaded project files? | C: | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Classify files by type (vision/charter, data models/specs, ETL strategies, KPI definitions, operational docs)"/><node TEXT="- Read each category and summarise the main points, requirements and decisions"/><node TEXT="- Capture any ambiguous or missing information as follow‑up questions or assumptions"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-003 | T:What major tasks, deliverables and questions emerge from the project documents for building the retail data warehouse and analytics solution? | C: | S:answered | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Compile tasks related to ETL meta tables, dimension seeding, merge procedures and staging loaders"/><node TEXT="- Identify higher‑level tasks like snapshot fact loading, SCD automation, performance benchmarking and dashboards"/><node TEXT="- List governance and operational deliverables such as CI/CD, documentation, KPI trace checks and runbook"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-004 | T:How should we map dependencies and decision points across the identified tasks and phases? | C: | S:answered | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Determine prerequisite relationships between tasks (e.g., dimensions before facts, ETL before dashboards)"/><node TEXT="- Identify decision points that influence downstream work (e.g., audit column design, spec choices)"/><node TEXT="- Choose a method to represent and track dependencies (e.g., YAML depends field, Gantt view)"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-005 | T:What roadmap should we follow to revisit and refine the Q‑Chain after the initial YAML compilation? | C: | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Schedule a post‑review cycle to cross‑check the YAML graph against the finalised documents"/><node TEXT="- Identify triggers for rework, such as new files, updated requirements or errors discovered during implementation"/><node TEXT="- Define the update mechanism and version control strategy for refining the YAML graph"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-ROOT | T:Set up the retail analytics project Q‑Chain | C: | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Define the project’s objective and initialise the Q‑Chain"/><node TEXT="- Spawn child questions covering document analysis, task identification and dependency mapping"/></node></node><node TEXT="tooling"><node TEXT="ID:Q-013 | T:How do we access and standardise project files across tools to avoid sandbox mismatches? | C:connectors | S:answered | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Select a canonical workspace for all I/O"/><node TEXT="- Add a session startup probe to verify mounts and filenames"/><node TEXT="- Define Drive→workspace import flow by folder ID"/><node TEXT="- Enforce ASCII‑hyphen naming and no spaces"/></node></node></node></map>